    David Adelman | Campus Apartments , LLC. | ZoomInfo.com David Adelman - Greenberg & BassDavid Adelman - Greenberg & Bass  (818) 382-6200      Select Page    David Adelman(818) 382-6200 Ext. 122 EmailDavid Adelman is a business lawyer. He assists clients with their real estate, corporate and intellectual property needs. He develops business strategies, provides business counsel and helps structure, negotiate and document business deals.Mr. Adelman fills the role of “outside” general counsel.  His clients span a vast array of industries, including aerospace, apparel, construction, distribution, education, energy, entertainment, fashion, financial services, fitness, food service, healthcare, hospitality, insurance, manufacturing, media, professional services, real estate, recycling, retail, software, technology and transportation.  He has been referred to as a “Renaissance Lawyer” – one whose expertise and experience span a significant number of different subject areas. He couples big firm work product with small firm sensibilities. Mr. Adelman holds community involvement in high regard.Mr. Adelman was selected to Super Lawyers in 2015 and 2016 for his work in the areas of Real Estate, Business/Corporate, and Intellectual Property. Representative MattersStructured the leasing program for a large shopping center management company with major regional mall holdings throughout the western U.S.Acquisition of a multi-million dollar hospital and medical office complex, including all related business assets.Acquired and disposed of property, secured development entitlements, drafted restrictive covenants, formed homeowners’ associations, managed design and construction issues and secured easements in connection with the development of two sizable residential resort communities in Puerto Rico.Represented a 120-person creditors committee in connection with a voluntary $6 million loan workout program, which included securitization work and on-going management of the disposition of the debtor’s portfolio of 50 multi-family residential properties.Secure and documented a $100 million line of credit for a nationally-recognized business liquidation and appraisal company.Represented a major e-commerce company in the formation of an Internet-based joint venture with a major entertainment company.Professional and Community Activities2015-2016 Southern California Super Lawyers, Super Lawyers Magazine2012 Attorney Trusted Advisor Award, San Fernando Valley Business Journal2012 Community Service Award, San Fernando Valley Business JournalChair, Valley Industry and Commerce Association (VICA)Board of Directors, Valley Presbyterian HospitalBoard of Directors, New HorizonsCounsel, Fit 4 The CauseBoard of Directors, Valley Economic AllianceBoard of Directors, Lambda Chi Alpha International Fraternity, Epsilon Sigma ChapterVolunteer, The Alliance for Children’s RightsMember, American Bar AssociationMember, Los Angeles County Bar AssociationMember, San Fernando Valley Bar AssociationLEED – Accredited ProfessionalEducationB.A., University of California at Los Angeles, 1977 J.D., Loyola Law School, 1984AdmissionsState of California United States District Court Central and Southern Districts of California United States District of Puerto Rico First and Ninth Circuit Courts of AppealsPublications & PostsJust What California Needs: A New Corporate Form Los Angeles Lawyer April 2011The Greening of Commercial Real Estate San Fernando Valley Business Journal September 15, 2008  


