	Management



David J. Adelman 
Vice Chairman
President and Chief Executive Officer, Campus Apartments Inc.

Mr. Adelman is the Chairman, co-founding partner of FS Investments and serves as Vice Chairman of the Board of Directors of FS Investment Corporation and as Vice Chairman of the Board of Trustees of FS Energy & Power Fund. He and Michael Forman were the lead investors in FS Investments. Mr. Adelman plays an integral role in developing and implementing investment strategies and providing platform solutions for the firm. He continues to use his experience and relationships to strengthen FS Investments.

Mr. Adelman is the President and CEO of Philadelphia-based Campus Apartments, Inc., and is one of the nation’s leading experts on student housing and a driving force in college and university real estate development. His long-term vision and aggressive growth plan drove Campus Apartments to where it is now: one of the largest privately held student housing companies in the country. Through strategic acquisitions, creative development, rehabilitation projects and the consolidation of owner-operators in various locales, Mr. Adelman has increased the company’s footprint to include properties in 25 states.

In addition to his duties as President and CEO of Campus Apartments, David Adelman is on the ICG (Nasdaq: ICGE) Board of Directors and is Vice Chair of University City District Board of Directors, a member of National Multi Family Council (NMHC), a member of the Young Presidents’ Organization, a member of Urban Land Institute’s Philadelphia Chapter and former President of the Apartment Association of Greater Philadelphia. Adelman was named the 2009 recipient of Multifamily Executive magazine’s prestigious “Executive of the Year” award. He was also selected as the 2010 Ernst & Young “Entrepreneur of the Year” in the real estate category in Greater Philadelphia.





















